{
	"nodes":[
		{
			"id":"3b877bbefa827ce2",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"Transform the character from the provided image into a standard A-pose.\n\nPose requirements:\n- Arms are slightly raised outward from the body at approximately 30–45 degrees.\n- Elbows are relaxed and slightly bent.\n- Hands are open and natural, with fingers slightly curved.\n- Legs are straight and slightly apart (hip-width distance).\n- Feet are flat and pointing forward.\n- The character stands upright in a neutral, balanced stance.\n\nCore constraints:\n- Preserve the exact character design, proportions, and silhouette.\n- Do NOT redesign, stylize, or modify any features.\n- Keep the same clothing, accessories, and details unchanged.\n- Maintain original body proportions (no stretching or shrinking).\n\nStyle preservation:\n- Keep the same art style, shading, and rendering as the original image.\n- Do not switch to realistic or different rendering styles.\n\nOutput:\n- Full-body character fully visible (no cropping).\n- Centered, with clean neutral background.\n- Even lighting, minimal shadows.\n\nImportant:\nThis is a pose adjustment only. The result must look like the same character repositioned into a proper A-pose, without any design changes.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-5000,
			"y":-7060,
			"width":1000,
			"height":860
		},
		{
			"id":"10c4284de228a170",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"Generate a clean, accurate 3-view orthographic reference (front, right side, back) of the main object from the provided image.\n\nCanvas & layout:\n- Use a horizontal 16:9 canvas.\n- Arrange the 3 views side-by-side (front, right side, back) from left to right.\n- Ensure all views fit completely within the frame (no cropping or truncation).\n- Leave sufficient padding around each view to avoid clipping any part of the object.\n- Maintain equal spacing between views and consistent margins.\n\nCore requirements:\n- Preserve the exact shape, proportions, and silhouette of the original object.\n- Maintain structural details and geometry consistency.\n- Do NOT redesign, stylize, or alter the object.\n- This is a reconstruction task, not a creative task.\n\nViews:\n- Provide 3 aligned views: front, right side, and back.\n- All views must be orthographic (no perspective distortion).\n- Ensure identical scale across all views.\n- Align all views on the same baseline and center.\n\nReconstruction:\n- Infer and reconstruct hidden or occluded parts logically.\n- Do not invent new features or modify the design.\n\nOutput style:\n- Clean white or transparent background.\n- Even lighting, minimal shadows.\n- Clear edges and readable structure.\n- High resolution, suitable for 3D modeling reference.\n\nImportant:\n- The object must be fully visible in all views (no parts cut off).\n- The result must represent the same object rotated into different views, with consistent proportions and accurate silhouette for modeling.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-4800,
			"y":-8457,
			"width":480,
			"height":901
		},
		{
			"id":"d60160605bc41084",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"Generate a clean 3-view orthographic reference (front, right side, back) of the main object from the provided image.\n\nCanvas & layout:\n- Use a horizontal 16:9 canvas.\n- Arrange the 3 views side-by-side from left to right: front, right side, back.\n- Ensure all views are fully visible within the frame (no cropping or truncation).\n- Add consistent padding around each view to prevent clipping.\n- Maintain equal spacing between the three views.\n- Scale the object so all views fit comfortably within the canvas (avoid excessive zoom).\n\nCore requirements:\n- Preserve the exact shape, proportions, and silhouette of the original object.\n- Maintain structural consistency and recognizable features.\n- Do NOT redesign or change the object identity.\n- Reconstruct hidden parts logically without adding new design elements.\n\n3-view constraints:\n- Provide front, right side, and back views.\n- Use orthographic projection (no perspective distortion).\n- Ensure all views are perfectly aligned and share identical scale.\n- Align all views to the same baseline and center axis.\n\nStyle transformation (IMPORTANT):\n- Convert the object into a stylized low-poly 3D look.\n- Match this style:\n  - Low polygon count geometry\n  - Smooth, rounded shapes (no sharp realism)\n  - Cartoon-like proportions (slightly exaggerated but consistent)\n  - Flat or soft gradient shading (non-photorealistic)\n  - Minimal texture detail, rely on color blocks\n  - Clean topology suitable for game assets\n  - Soft studio lighting with gentle shadows\n- The final result should resemble a stylized mobile game asset.\n\nOutput style:\n- Neutral background (white or light gradient).\n- Even lighting, minimal shadow noise.\n- Clear silhouette for modeling reference.\n- High resolution.\n\nImportant:\n- The object must be fully visible in all views (no parts cut off).\n- Do NOT zoom into the object.\n- This is NOT a realistic reconstruction.\n- This is NOT a redesign.\n- It is the SAME object, converted into a low-poly stylized 3D form and shown in 3 orthographic views.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-4301,
			"y":-8506,
			"width":602,
			"height":1020
		},
		{
			"id":"e1c456a8e4fde4d9",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"Generate a clean, accurate 3-view orthographic reference (front, right side, back) of the main object from the provided image.\n- Use a horizontal 16:9 canvas.\nCore requirements:\n- Preserve the exact shape, proportions, and silhouette of the original object.\n- Maintain structural details and geometry consistency.\n- Do NOT redesign, stylize, or alter the object.\n- This is a reconstruction task, not a creative task.\n\nViews:\n- Provide 3 aligned views: front, right side, and back.\n- All views must be orthographic (no perspective distortion).\n- Ensure identical scale across all views.\n- Align all views on the same baseline and center.\n\nReconstruction:\n- Infer and reconstruct hidden or occluded parts logically.\n- Do not invent new features or modify the design.\n\nOutput style:\n- Clean white or transparent background.\n- Even lighting, minimal shadows.\n- Clear edges and readable structure.\n- High resolution, suitable for 3D modeling reference.\n\nImportant:\nThe result must represent the same object rotated into different views, with consistent proportions and accurate silhouette for modeling.",
