		{
			"id":"5e516a1cc570e993",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"Transform the character from the provided image into a standard A-pose.\n\nPose requirements:\n\n- Arms raised outward at approximately 30–45 degrees.\n\n- Elbows slightly bent and relaxed.\n\n- Hands open with natural finger curvature.\n\n- Legs straight and slightly apart (hip-width).\n\n- Feet flat and pointing forward.\n\n- Spine upright in a neutral standing position.\n\nSTRICT geometry constraints (CRITICAL):\n\n- Preserve EXACT proportions, height, width, and silhouette of the character.\n\n- Maintain pixel-accurate scale relative to the original.\n\n- Do NOT stretch, shrink, thicken, or thin any body part.\n\n- Do NOT alter head-to-body ratio, limb length, or torso proportions.\n\n- Preserve the exact outer contour (silhouette must match the original when overlapped).\n\n- Keep all clothing, accessories, and details in the exact same size and placement.\n\nTransformation rules:\n\n- ONLY change joint rotations (pose adjustment).\n\n- Do NOT modify mesh structure or geometry.\n\n- Do NOT redesign or reinterpret any part of the character.\n\nStyle preservation:\n\n- Keep identical art style, shading, colors, and rendering.\n\n- Do not introduce realism or new stylistic elements.\n\nOutput:\n\n- Full-body character fully visible (no cropping).\n\n- Centered and scaled consistently (no zoom distortion).\n\n- Clean neutral background.\n\n- Even lighting, minimal shadows.\n\nImportant:\n\n- This is a STRICT pose retargeting task.\n\n- The result must look like the exact same character rotated into an A-pose, not a recreated version.\n\n- Any deviation in proportions, height, or silhouette is NOT allowed.\n\nEnsure joint rotations are anatomically correct and suitable for rigging.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-4160,
			"y":-7389,
			"width":800,
			"height":860
		},
